        <detaileddescription>
<para>returns string representation of the current stacktrace; the function is inlined, to put the code in any shared library; if std::stacktrace is first called from MRMesh.dll then it is not unloaded propely Generated from function <computeroutput>MR::getCurrentStacktraceInline</computeroutput>. Never returns null. Returns an instance allocated on the heap! Must call <computeroutput>MR_std_string_Destroy()</computeroutput> to free it when you&apos;re done using it. </para>
